cs.RO, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.CV, cs.OH 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a method for tracking algal blooms using autonomous surface robots and presents a multi-agent control algorithm for the continuous monitoring of the dynamic evolution of the algal bloom. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is also likely as the paper proposes a decentralized least squares estimation of the target and a controller for circumnavigation, which involves multiple agents working together. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper presents a control algorithm for the robots to circumnavigate the algal bloom. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a possible category as the paper mentions the use of satellite images to indicate the existence and initial location of the algal bloom. 
- cs.OH (Other Computer Science) is a less likely category as the paper is focused on a specific application (algal bloom tracking) and presents a method and algorithm for achieving this goal.
